  <div class="col-xl-9 col-lg-8 main_header_content">
    <h2 class="title">About Me</h2>
    <p>
      Hi 👋 ! I am Farnaz or in short Naz. I identify myself as an interdisciplinary researcher specialising in landscape and heritage studies, with a focus on
      how cultural and environmental knowledge of landscapes is produced, interpreted, and
      translated into heritage policy and planning. 
    </p>
    <p>
      Recently I have been graduated from VUA with a PhD in History and Heritage of Cultural landscape and Urban Environments, and an associate researcher (not employed) at Newcastle University. I am looking for any teaching or Research opportunities. 
    </p>

    <h2 class="title">Research Interest</h2>
    <p>
      My main interest in the following topics lies in the intersection of the policy, research and community enagegement. 
    </p>
     <ul>
      <li>
        Urban Heritage Conservation, Management and Policy,
      </li>
      <li> 
        Landscapes, whether historic, industrial or cultural landscapes research, policy, 
      </li>
      <li>
        Spatial Analysis using GIS, PPGIS, AI based tools,
      </li>
      <li>
       Creative and Participatory based approaches in Research such as Walking interviews, oral histories, Crafts etc.,
      </li>
      <li>
        Place-making and Planning in Mixed and Marginalised neighbourhoods (such as immigrants, working class, ghettos, etc),
      </li>
      <li>
        Architecture and Urbanism History, Theory and Heritage, particularly in the WENA, Europeoan Context,
      </li>
    </ul>

